## Why This Matters

1. **Inference Speed** — Smaller KV cache = better cache locality = fewer GPU memory reads
2. **Throughput** — More concurrent requests on the same hardware
3. **Cost** — Run larger models on smaller GPUs
4. **Edge Deployment** — Make LLMs practical on mobile and IoT devices

## Conclusion

TurboQuant represents a paradigm shift in LLM deployment efficiency. By combining polar coordinate mapping (PolarQuant) with 1-bit correction (QJL), Google achieved lossless 6x compression of the KV cache without training or tuning.

This is production-ready, and the community has already begun integration into frameworks like vLLM, Ollama, and HuggingFace Transformers.

The future of LLM inference is here. 🚀
